13:[["$","p",null,{"children":"One of the trickiest parts of web design is getting components to adapt not just to the viewport but to their own container sizes. Wouldn't it be great if elements could respond to the space they're actually given?"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Well, good news! CSS Container Queries are here to save the day."}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"The Limitations of Media Queries"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Media queries have been the backbone of responsive design for years. They allow us to apply styles based on the viewport's dimensions, which is great for adjusting layouts on different devices. But here's the catch: media queries only consider the viewport, not the actual size of an element's container."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Imagine you have a reusable card component that looks great in one section of your site but doesn't quite fit in another due to different container sizes. With media queries alone, adjusting the card for each context becomes a nightmare."}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"Enter Container Queries"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Container Queries enable elements to adapt their styling based on the size of their parent container. This means your components can be truly modular and context-aware, adjusting themselves no matter where they're placed."}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"How Do Container Queries Work?"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["First things first, you need to designate an element as a container. You do this using the ",["$","code",null,{"children":"container-type"}]," property."]}],"\n",["$","pre",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"hljs language-css","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-selector-class","children":".container"}]," {\n  container-type: inline-size;\n}\n"]}]}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"children":"container-type: inline-size"}]}],": This tells the browser to consider the container's inline size (usually width in left-to-right languages)."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"children":"container-type: size"}]}],": This considers both the inline size and block size (width and height)."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Once you've set up your container, you can write styles that respond to its size using the ",["$","code",null,{"children":"@container"}]," rule."]}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"A Practical Example"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Let's build a responsive card component that adapts based on its container's width."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Try resizing the card below using the resize handle to see how the text wraps based on the container's horizontal width. When the card is wider than 500px, the text and image will be displayed side by side. When it's narrower, the text will wrap below the image."}],"\n",["$","$L14",null,{}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["$","strong",null,{"children":"HTML Structure"}]}],"\n",["$","pre",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"hljs language-html","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-tag","children":["<",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-name","children":"div"}]," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-attr","children":"class"}],"=",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-string","children":"\"card-container\""}],">"]}],"\n  ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-tag","children":["<",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-name","children":"div"}]," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-attr","children":"class"}],"=",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-string","children":"\"card\""}],">"]}],"\n    ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-tag","children":["<",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-name","children":"img"}]," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-attr","children":"src"}],"=",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-string","children":"\"image.jpg\""}]," />"]}],"\n    ",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-tag","children":["<",["$","span",null,{"className":"hljs-name","children":"div"}]," ","$L15","=","$L16",">"]}],"\n      ","$L17","Card Title","$L18","\n      ","$L19","This is some sample text to illustrate the card component.","$L1a","\n    ","$L1b","\n  ","$L1c","\n","$L1d","\n"]}]}],"\n","$L1e","\n","$L1f","\n","$L20","\n","$L21","\n","$L22","\n","$L23","\n","$L24","\n","$L25","\n","$L26","\n","$L27","\n","$L28","\n","$L29","\n","$L2a","\n","$L2b","\n","$L2c","\n","$L2d","\n","$L2e","\n","$L2f","\n","$L30","\n","$L31","\n","$L32","\n","$L33","\n","$L34","\n","$L35"]
